snippet.textDisplay:
) Falun Gong practitioners and supporters rallied in front of the Customs House building in downtown Sydney on January 31, 2020. They wanted to raise awareness of the persecution of the spiritual group in China and to celebrate the 350 million Chinese people who have withdrawn from the Communist Party (CCP) and its affiliated organizations.

The day of activities started with practitioners demonstrating the five sets of exercises on the plaza in front of the customs building in the early morning and was followed by a rally and speeches.

Due to the outbreak of the coronavirus in China, fewer Chinese tourists have been coming to this popular tourist site. Some Chinese tourists were still around, though, and they listened to the speeches at the rally and took fliers. Some said they would quit the communist party online.

A Chinese Australian came to the rally and gave an impromptu speech after reading an announcement about the event in the Epoch Times.

Chinese Australian: I want to express my respect to the Falun Gong group!
